    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-09-26</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2007-11-02T21:15:19Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Medicare Independent Living Act of 2007 - Amends title XVIII (Medicare) of the Social Security Act to eliminate the in-the-home restriction for Medicare coverage of mobility devices for individuals with expected long-term needs. Deems such devices to be durable medical equipment (DME) if they are used in customary settings for the purpose of normal domestic, vocational, or community activities.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
